OL,3,CFalklands becomes political football
OL,4,Cahead of Argentina and England grudge
OL,5,Cmatch
OL,7,FArgentina's president, Milei, a far-
OL,8,Fright economist, has insisted the
OL,9,Fislands "were, are and will always be
OL,10,FArgentine", while his vice-president,
OL,11,FVictoria Villarruel, told all Britons
OL,12,Fliving there to "go back to England".
OL,14,FDowning Street insists sovereignty of
OL,15,Fthe Falklands is "not in question".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
