OL,3,CFalklands becomes political football
OL,4,Cahead of Argentina and England grudge
OL,5,Cmatch
OL,7,FA quarter-final - known in Argentina
OL,8,Fas "the robbery of the century" -
OL,9,Fquickly spiralled into a kicking
OL,10,Fcontest.
OL,12,FIt was settled by a Geoff Hurst
OL,13,Fheader, which the Argentinians still
OL,14,Fbelieve was offside.
OL,16,FEngland manager Sir Alf described
OL,17,Ftheir opponents as "animals" when they
OL,18,Fsurrounded the referee, who had to be
OL,19,Fescorted off by police. He then
OL,20,Fstopped his players from exchanging
OL,21,Fshirts.
OL,26,@pD@DOUpD@_O]yD@TOUyD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
