OL,3,CFalklands becomes political football
OL,4,Cahead of Argentina and England grudge
OL,5,Cmatch
OL,7,F"This is what dreams are made of.
OL,8,FEveryone as a little boy dreamt of
OL,9,Fplaying and winning a World Cup.
OL,11,F"We're against one of the best nations
OL,12,Fin the semi-final."
OL,14,FEngland captain Harry Kane said of the
OL,15,Ftie: "We'll be playing against one of
OL,16,Fthe best teams in the world in the
OL,17,Fsemi-final, so the most pleasing thing
OL,18,Fis that we are in a semi-final and we
OL,19,Fcan still feel like we can improve."
